title: Drone Workshop
description: A quadcopter (also called a quadrotor helicopter) is a multi-rotor helicopter lifted and propelled by four rotors. Classified as rotorcraft, they generate lift through vertically oriented rotors. Typically using two clockwise (CW) and two counterclockwise (CCW) fixed-pitch propellers, they achieve control by varying each rotor's speed. This allows manipulation of thrust, position, and torque.
